theorem
Th35: (for perm being (Element of ( Permutations n )) holds (nt1 = ( nt2 * perm ) implies (( Det ( Segm (M,nt1,nt) ) ) = ( - (( Det ( Segm (M,nt2,nt) ) ),perm) ) & ( Det ( Segm (M,nt,nt1) ) ) = ( - (( Det ( Segm (M,nt,nt2) ) ),perm) ))))
proof
let perm being (Element of ( Permutations n ));
assume that
A1: nt1 = ( nt2 * perm );
reconsider Perm = perm as (Permutation of ( Seg n )) by MATRIX_2:def 9;
( Segm (M,nt1,nt) ) = ( ( Segm (M,nt2,nt) ) * Perm ) by A1,CKB34:1;
hence ( Det ( Segm (M,nt1,nt) ) ) = ( - (( Det ( Segm (M,nt2,nt) ) ),perm) ) by MATRIX11:46;
thus ( Det ( Segm (M,nt,nt1) ) ) = ( Det ( ( Segm (M,nt,nt1) ) @ ) ) by MATRIXR2:43
.= ( Det ( ( ( Segm (M,nt,nt2) ) @ ) * Perm ) ) by A1,CKB35:1
.= ( - (( Det ( ( Segm (M,nt,nt2) ) @ ) ),perm) ) by MATRIX11:46
.= ( - (( Det ( Segm (M,nt,nt2) ) ),perm) ) by MATRIXR2:43;
end;
